### Formula Structure
- **Liu Jun Zi Tang base**: Ren Shen + Bai Zhu + Fu Ling + Gan Cao + Chen Pi + Ban Xia (tonify qi, resolve phlegm)
- **Aromatic addition**: Mu Xiang + Sha Ren (regulate qi, enhance digestive function)

## üéØ Clinical Applications

### Primary Pattern & Manifestations
**Pattern**: Spleen qi deficiency with qi stagnation and phlegm-dampness
**Key Symptoms**: Poor appetite, abdominal distension, nausea, loose stools, fatigue, feeling of incomplete digestion, belching, borborygmus
**Tongue**: Pale with thick white coating
**Pulse**: Deep, weak, and possibly slippery

### Secondary Applications
- Chronic gastritis with digestive weakness
- Functional dyspepsia
- Chronic diarrhea with spleen deficiency
- Post-illness digestive recovery
- Chronic fatigue with digestive issues
- Loss of appetite in elderly

### Modern Clinical Uses
- Functional gastrointestinal disorders
- Chronic gastritis and gastroparesis
- Irritable bowel syndrome with constipation/diarrhea
- Post-operative digestive recovery
- Chronic fatigue syndrome with GI symptoms
- Elderly digestive weakness

## üìù Therapeutic Actions
**Primary**: Tonify qi, strengthen spleen, regulate qi, resolve dampness

**Secondary**: Improve appetite, enhance digestion, reduce bloating, restore energy

## üîÑ Modifications & Variations

### Common Additions
| Condition | Add Herbs | Rationale |
|-----------|-----------|-----------|
| Severe qi deficiency | Huang Qi + Da Zao | Stronger qi tonification |
| Cold constitution | Gan Jiang + Ding Xiang | Warm the middle jiao |
| Poor appetite | Shan Zha + Shen Qu | Enhance digestive enzymes |
| Chronic diarrhea | Rou Dou Kou + He Zi | Astringe intestines |

### Classical Variations
- **Si Jun Zi Tang**: Remove Chen Pi, Ban Xia, Mu Xiang, Sha Ren (simpler qi tonification)
- **Liu Jun Zi Tang**: Remove Mu Xiang and Sha Ren (qi tonification with phlegm resolution)
- **With warming herbs**: Add Gan Jiang for cold stomach

### Modern Modifications
- For gastroparesis: Add Ji Nei Jin and Mai Ya
- For IBS: Add Bai Shao and Gan Cao
- For chronic fatigue: Add Wu Wei Zi and Huang Qi

